  note =	 {The 15th International Conference on Electronic
                  Properties of Two-Dimensional Systems(EP2DS) Nara,
                  Japan},
  year =	 2003,
  annote =	 { The device, shown in the SEM photograph, was made
                  on a Si substrate with a SiO2 buffer layer. E-beam
                  lithography and shadow evaporation were used to
                  fabricate an SET inside an aluminum/niobium
                  ring. The ring defines a pool of helium, 0.8 ?m deep
                  and 3 ?m diameter as an electron trap. The
                  superconducting Al/AlO3/Al SET is operated at the
                  Josephson-Quasiparticle peak (JQP) for maximum
                  sensitivity. Coulomb blockade oscillations (CBO) in
                  the SET source-drain current are generated by
                  sweeping the gate and guard electrodes. Electrons
