                  indicates the noise threshold as well as other
                  information. It is found that concatenated codes
                  based on the [[23,1,7]] Golay code give higher
                  thresholds than those based on the [[7,1,3]] Hamming
                  code under most conditions. The threshold gate noise
                  0 is a function of µ/³ and tm; example values are
