                  information processing is discussed. Three-state and
                  higher-dimensional quantum systems are known to have
                  very different properties from two-state
                  systemsâ€”i.e., qubits. In particular there exist
                  qudit states which are not equivalent under local
                  unitary transformations unless a selection rule is
                  violated. This observation is shown to be an
